@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Terms of Service";
}
<div class="container py-5">
    <div class="auth-card mx-auto shadow-lg" style="max-width: 900px; padding: 4rem;">
        <div class="text-center mb-5">
            <h1 class="fw-black text-dark" style="letter-spacing: -2px; font-size: 3rem;">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
            <p class="text-muted fw-bold">Last Revised: May 5, 2026</p>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-content fw-bold text-muted" style="line-height: 1.8;">
            
            <section class="mb-5">
                <h4 class="text-dark fw-black text-uppercase small mb-3" style="letter-spacing: 1px;">1. Acceptance of Terms</h4>
                <p>
                    By accessing NipponQuest, you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service. If you do not agree to all terms,
                    you are prohibited from using the service. This platform is provided "as is" for educational and
                    entertainment purposes.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-5">
                <h4 class="text-dark fw-black text-uppercase small mb-3" style="letter-spacing: 1px;">2. User Conduct & Fair Play</h4>
                <p>To maintain the integrity of our Leagues, Leaderboards, and Discover Hub, you agree not to:</p>
                <ul class="list-unstyled ps-3 border-start border-primary border-3">
                    <li class="mb-2"><strong>Cheat:</strong> Use automated scripts, bots, or exploits to gain XP or Gold.</li>
                    <li class="mb-2"><strong>Upload Malicious Content:</strong> Distribute viruses, malware, or corrupted data through Anki deck (.apkg) uploads.</li>
                    <li class="mb-2"><strong>Impersonate:</strong> Choose a GamerTag that is offensive, copyrighted, or impersonates another user or staff member.</li>
                    <li class="mb-2"><strong>Disrupt:</strong> Attempt to interfere with the site’s security or performance.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-5">
                <h4 class="text-dark fw-black text-uppercase small mb-3" style="letter-spacing: 1px;">3. User-Generated Content & Discover Hub</h4>
                <p>
                    By publishing flashcard decks or any other content to the <strong>Discover Hub</strong>, you grant NipponQuest a non-exclusive, royalty-free license to host, display, and distribute that content to other users.
                    You represent that you own or have the necessary rights to the content you upload. We reserve the right to remove any decks that violate copyright laws, contain inappropriate material, or are deemed harmful, without prior notice.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-5">
                <h4 class="text-dark fw-black text-uppercase small mb-3" style="letter-spacing: 1px;">4. Virtual Economy (Gold)</h4>
                <p>
                    "Gold" earned through gameplay, streaks, or selling decks on the Discover Hub is a virtual currency strictly for use within the NipponQuest platform.
                    It holds <strong>no real-world monetary value</strong>, cannot be redeemed for cash, and cannot be transferred or sold outside of the platform's official ecosystem.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-5">
                <h4 class="text-dark fw-black text-uppercase small mb-3" style="letter-spacing: 1px;">5. Intellectual Property</h4>
                <p>
                    All code, designs, and brand assets (including the "NipponQuest" name and logos) are the exclusive property of
                    <strong>Joshua Marc Lourens</strong>. You may not reproduce or distribute any part of this platform without
                    explicit written consent. You retain ownership of the original educational content you create and upload.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-5">
                <h4 class="text-dark fw-black text-uppercase small mb-3" style="letter-spacing: 1px;">6. Account Termination</h4>
                <p>
                    We reserve the right to suspend or terminate your account and forfeit all associated XP, uploaded decks, and Gold balances
                    at our sole discretion, without notice, for conduct that we believe violates these Terms or is harmful to
                    other users of the platform.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-5">
                <h4 class="text-dark fw-black text-uppercase small mb-3" style="letter-spacing: 1px;">7. Limitation of Liability</h4>
                <p>
                    In no event shall NipponQuest or its developer be liable for any damages (including, without limitation,
                    damages for loss of data or profit) arising out of the use or inability to use the materials on this website.
                    We do not guarantee the accuracy of language translations, user-uploaded flashcards, or quest content.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-5">
                <h4 class="text-dark fw-black text-uppercase small mb-3" style="letter-spacing: 1px;">8. Governing Law</h4>
                <p>
                    Any claim relating to NipponQuest shall be governed by the laws of <strong>South Africa</strong>, without regard
                    to its conflict of law provisions. You agree to submit to the personal and exclusive jurisdiction of the
                    courts located within Westville, KwaZulu-Natal.
                </p>
            </section>

            <div class="mt-5 pt-4 border-top text-center">
                <p class="small opacity-75">
                    For legal or technical inquiries: <br />
                    <span class="text-dark fw-black">YugenLabs</span><br />
                    <span class="text-muted">Lead Developer: Joshua Marc Lourens</span><br />
                    Westville, South Africa
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>